We therefore retraced our steps to the southward. The ice that had so much impeded our progress upward, had entirely disappeared. We touched for refreshments by the way, at some of the settlements on the coast of Greenland, where we were most kindly and hospitably received by the Danish authorities,

Leaving Holsteinberg on the 6th of September for New York, the two vessels were separated in a gale to the southward of Cape Farewell. The Advance arrived on the 3011: ultimo, and the Rescue on the vth inst„
